<HEADLINE> Road Accidents Claim 15 Lives in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, December 26 (Xinhua) -- Fifteen people have died and
122 others have been wounded in 215 road accidents countrywide
since the current festive season began on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
A police spokesman said here today that Harare Province had
the highest number of road accidents with 111. Three people were
killed and 29 others injured in Harare alone.
</P>
<P>
He said that negligence, drunken driving, speeding, vehicle
defects and fatigue were the major causes of the road accidents.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile the police highway patrols have so far issued 781
tickets for various offences amounting to 24,000 U. S. Dollars.
</P>
