<HEADLINE> Thai Constitution Drafting Assembly Elected </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 26 (Xinhua) -- The Thai parliament today
finalized the 99 members for the constitution drafting assembly,
marking the formal establishment of the panel which will write a
new constitution for the country.
</P>
<P>
The 99-member panel was elected at a joint meeting of the House
of Representatives and the Senate.
</P>
<P>
The decision to draft the new constitution was determined by
the parliament in mid-September this year as part of the political
reform in the country.
</P>
<P>
The 99 member panel consisted of 76 representatives from
Thailand's 76 provinces, with each represented by one, and 23 from
academic circles in the country.
</P>
<P>
The new charter will be Thailand's 16th version since 1932 when
a constitutional monarchy came into being in the country.
</P>
<P>
The draft constitution will be submitted to the Thai parliament
for deliberation after it is completed. If the draft fails to pass
the parliament, it will be subject to a referendum.  
</P>
</TEXT>
