<TEXT>
<P>
Johannesburg, December 26 (Xinhua) -- South African Minister
of Safety and Security Sidney Mufamadi said on Thursday those
behind Tuesday's bomb attacks near Cape Town will severely be
punished.
</P>
<P>
Mufamadi said the bloody incident is a show of rebellion against
the committment of President Melson Mandela's government to
reconciliation.
</P>
<P>
At least three people were killed and 80 others injured on
Christmas Eve when three bombs exploded at a shopping center in
Worcester, 100 milometers from Cape Town. Most of the victims
were children.
</P>
<P>
The bomb explosions, believed to have been caused by home-made
bombs, have also caused great damage to properties of the shopping
complex.
</P>
<P>
An investigation team has been put together to track down the
perpetrators of the bomb attacks.
</P>
<P>
