<HEADLINE> Summit of African First Ladies Billed for Early </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lagos, December 26 (Xinhua) -- A summit of African first
ladies is to be convened in the first quarter of next year.
</P>
<P>
The News Agency of Nigerian today quoted Nigeria's first lady,
Mrs. Maryam Abacha, as saying that the proposals at the West
African Ladies' Summit held recently in Nigeria have been sent to
all African first ladies to enable them to appreciate the need
for the forthcoming summit.
</P>
<P>
On using the first ladies forum to enhance peace in the
continent, Mrs. Abacha said the problems of conflict differ from
one country to another and special approaches would be needed in
each of the cases.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the first ladies should hold regional meetings to
prepare for the continental one just like "we did in west
Africa," she said at a recent forum in Abuja, capital of Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
"There are countries with their own peculiar problems, so a
very mature approach is needed," she said, quoted by the offical
news agency.  
</P>
</TEXT>
