<HEADLINE> 7 People Killed in Car Bomb in Algiers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, December 26 (Xinhua) -- At least seven people were
killed and 70 others wounded in a car bomb blast in the Algerian
capital of Algiers today, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
The report said the explosion, the second of the type in the
week, took place near a a police station at 1:45 p.m. (12:45 GMT).
</P>
<P>
Five cars and a bus were destroyed in Hussein-Day area and
nearby buildings were also damaged.
</P>
<P>
The injured, most of whom were pedestrians and motorists, were
rushed to nearby hospitals, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
The incident was on the heel of another one in Algiers three
days ago which killed three people and wounded 70.
</P>
<P>
No one has claimed responsibility for either the attack.
</P>
<P>
Muslim militants in Algeria have been fighting for the setting
up of a government based on Islamic law for five years, resulting
in the deaths of more than 60,000 people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
