<HEADLINE> Workshop on Mountain Tourism to Be Held in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, December 27 (Xinhua) -- A mountain tourism
organization in Nepal is to hold a workshop on ecology-friendly
trekking activities early next month to generate awareness of
mountain ecology among tourists and tour operators, organizers
announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The two-day eco-trekking workshop, organized here by the
Trekking Agents Association of Nepal (TAAN) on January 2 and 3,
will familiarize participants with the growing trekking activities
in the country's mountainous region and their possible impact on
the natural environment.
</P>
<P>
The program, to be attended by tourists, trekking guides and
local representatives, will also discuss ways to preserve mountain
environment while promoting trekking activities, the TAAN said.
</P>
<P>
Participants at the workshop are expected to be trained in high
altitude sickness treatment, solid waste management, first aid,
health and sanitation, alternative energy use, and preservation of
natural and cultural heritage.
</P>
<P>
The tourism industry in Nepal is becoming more aware about the
need to preserve mountain ecology for the promotion and
sustainable development of tourism, one of Nepal's major sources
of foreign exchange earnings, TAAN sources said.
</P>
<P>
According to them, TAAN members include over half of the
existing 300 trekking agencies in the country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
