<HEADLINE> 23 million Bangladeshis Exposed to Arsenic Poisoning </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, December 27 (Xinhua) -- About 23 million Bangladeshis
are exposed to arsenic poisoning by drinking arsenic-contaminated
water, according to experts here.
</P>
<P>
A study conducted recently by doctors and scientists from India
and Bangladesh revealed that arsenic presence has been found in 44
out of total 107 thanas (police stations, lower-level
administrative body under the district) in 16 districts of the
country.
</P>
<P>
The experts noted that the 44 thanas covering an area of 12,420
square kilometers where the study was conducted are located in
different parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
"The arsenic calamity of Bangladesh can only be brought under
control if the withdrawal of ground water is restricted and proper
utilization of surface water is made," the study suggested.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
