<HEADLINE> Bangladesh's Biggest Art Exhibition Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, December 27 (Xinhua) -- The 12th national art exhibition
of Bangladesh opened here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina formally inaugurated the
three-week long art extravaganza, the biggest of its kind in terms
of the number of participants, the total number of displays, the
volume of prizes and awards distributed, and the variety and
technical novelty of the works.
</P>
<P>
A total of 213 fine arts practitioners from all over the
country are participating in the exhibition to display 258 pieces
of works.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on the occasion, the prime minister called upon
artists to innovate objects and ideas attuned to the urge of the
modern age, keeping complete adherence to the history, tradition
and cultural heritage of the nation.  
