<HEADLINE> China to Accelerate Development of Coal Gas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, November 27 (Xinhua) -- China is to offer
preferential treatment for the development of coal gas, known as
coalbed methane, said a senior official with the Ministry of Coal
Industry today.
</P>
<P>
To accelerate the development of the new energy, the government
will not collect a compensation fee for the development of coal
gas for a period of time, and will give priority in extending
loans to key development projects, said the official who is
attending a national conference on coal production.
</P>
<P>
Coal gas is a "green energy" with large development potential,
the official said, adding that the development of coal gas is of
great significance to the improvement of China's energy structure,
environmental protection, and the improvement of safety conditions
in coal mining.
</P>
<P>
China has a huge deposit of coal gas resources. In the
northern, northeastern and the southern parts of the country
alone, exploitable coal gas resources amount to 3.5 billion cubic
meters.
</P>
<P>
With state investment and foreign loans, China has set up more
than 50 coal-gas development projects, building gas-holders with a
total volume of 650,000 cubic meters and transportation pipelines
with a total length of 620,000 meters.
</P>
<P>
The country currently uses more than 400 million cubic meters
of coal gas annually, the official said.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that China has developed a complete set of
coal gas technology. More than 20 items of technology have met
world-advanced levels.
</P>
<P>
Sino-foreign cooperation is an important driving force behind
the development of coal gas, he noted.
</P>
<P>
In recent years the United Nations Development Program has
provided 10 million US dollars in financial assistance for the
country's three model coal gas projects, and another project for
appraising the country's coal gas resources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
