<HEADLINE> Shanghai Opens Largest Club With Taiwan Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 27 (Xinhua) -- A showpiece club that boasts
its own ballet troupe and orchestra has opened in China's largest
city Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Golden Age International Business Membership Club,
based in Huaihai Road, a major commercial street in the city, is
the largest entertainment center in Shanghai, with investment
coming from Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Built at a cost of 40 million yuan (about 5 million US
dollars), the club has an area of 2,000 square meters, which
includes a ballroom that can hold 300 guests and 21 karaoke suites.
</P>
<P>
It has also formed a 20-piece orchestra and invited 10 Russian
professional dancers to perform ballet classics for the guests
every night.
</P>
<P>
Johnny Y.T. Chang, board director of the club, expressed
confidence in the club's future.
</P>
<P>
"We don't have to worry about our business, since there are
nearly 20,000 overseas-funded enterprises and about 10,000 foreign
households of permanent residence in Shanghai, as well as over one
million overseas tourists each year," claimed the Taiwan
businessman.
</P>
<P>
There are currently 5,810 entertainment centers attracting
nearly 200,000 visitors every day in Shanghai, which opened its
first ballroom and music bar in 1984.  
</P>
</TEXT>
