<HEADLINE> France to Withdraw from Turkey-Based Allied Force </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 27 (Xinhua) -- France today formally announced
its withdrawal from the Turkey-based allied air force assigned to
protect the Kurdish population in northern Iraq.
</P>
<P>
A French Foreign Ministry communique said that France will not
participate in the new allied air force which will replace from
January 1, 1997, the "Provide Comfort" mission launched by the
United States, Britain, France and Turkey after the 1991 Gulf War.
</P>
<P>
France disputed with the United States over a number of issues,
including the U.S. missile attacks on Iraq in September and the
extension of the no-fly zone in southern Iraq.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish parliament voted earlier this week for the creation
of the new allied force to be deployed in southern Turkey, while
the "Provide Comfort" ends its mission at the end of the year.
</P>
</TEXT>
