<HEADLINE> Beijing Holds Farewell Ceremony for Deceased Playwright </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 27 (Xinhua) -- People from all walks of life
in Beijing gathered at a suburban cemetery here to attend a
ceremony of farewell to Cao Yu, the country's top playwright who
passed away two weeks ago at the age of 86.
</P>
<P>
Lying in peace in the memorial hall of the Babaoshan Cemetery,
the body of Cao was encircled by flowers, with his favorite tune,
Chopin's "The Funeral", being played in the background.
</P>
<P>
Present were Party and government leaders Li Ruihuan, Ding
Guangen, Li Tieying and Wei Jianxing.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin, premier Li Peng, and other top
leaders sent wreaths to extend their condolences over the death of
the great playwright.
</P>
<P>
Earning an early reputation in 1934 for his first play
"Thunderstorm", Cao has been regarded as the founding father of
China's modern dramas, and was executive president of the China
Federation of Literary and Art Circles when he died on December 14.
</P>
<P>
He is survived by his wife and four daughters, who also
attended today's ceremony.  
</P>
</TEXT>
