<HEADLINE> Tourism To Become Guangzhou's Pillar Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 27 (Xinhua) -- A top tourism official in
Guangzhou, capital of south China's Guangdong Province, announced
today that tourism will become a pillar industry in the city next
year.
</P>
<P>
The number of tourists received by the major hotels in the city
is expected to reach 15.27 million this year, including 2.27
million overseas visitors, increasing by 15 percent and nine
percent over the past year, according to Liu Ping, director of the
city's tourism bureau.
</P>
<P>
Tourism has earned the city 920 million US dollars, with the
total business turnover reaching 13 billion yuan this year,
increases of eight percent and 19 percent over the year 1995,
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The city's tourism income now accounts for 10 percent of the
country's total, with over 8.5 percent of the city's Gross
National Product coming from tourism industry.
</P>
<P>
To further boost its development, efforts will be made to train
professionals in the tourism industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
