<HEADLINE> China, Russia Agree on Summit in April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 27 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng and
Russian President Boris Yeltsin today agreed to hold a summit
meeting between the presidents of the two countries in Moscow next
April.
</P>
<P>
Li was the first foreign visitor to meet the Russian leader
since Yeltsin's return to the Kremlin on Monday after a major
heart surgery on November 5.
</P>
<P>
The one-hour meeting in the Kremlin covered a number of issues
over bilateral relations, but on top of the agenda was the planned
Chinese-Russian summit between President Jiang Zemin and Yeltsin.
</P>
<P>
Li said the forthcoming visit by Jiang would be of great
importance to the further development of bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
The premier conveyed Jiang's greetings to Yeltsin and said
Chinese leaders are very glad to see that the Russian president
had recovered from the operation and resumed his work in the
Kremlin.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin thanked Chinese leaders for their greetings and said he
is looking forward to Jiang's visit.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin expressed satisfaction with the current Sino-Russian
relations. He said the two countries have pushed their relations
to a new level of development.
</P>
<P>
"The strategic agreements, achieved between us, are working,"
he said, referring to Li's current Moscow trip which marks the
inauguration of a regular meeting mechanism between Chinese and
Russian premiers.
</P>
<P>
Li arrived in Moscow Thursday for a two-day working visit,
during which he is also expected to hold talks with his Russian
counterpart, Viktor Chernomyrdin, and sign a number of documents
on economic cooperation between the two countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
