close eye on problems emerging after the country adopted the
reform and opening-up policy in 1978.
</P>
<P>
He said that procurators should take full advantage of all
legal weapons, in a bid to strike a hard blow to crimes which
hamper the country's reform, and safeguard the healthy development
of the socialist market economy.
</P>
<P>
Zhang asked procuratorial organs nationwide to strengthen their
awareness of investigation and evidence, and grasp the
characteristics of major corruption cases to help them adapt to
the needs of the country's anti-corruption drive. 
