<HEADLINE> Macao Population Grows to 455,000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 27 (Xinhua) -- Macao's total population grew
to 455,000 by August 30, 1996, statistics show.
</P>
<P>
Figures released by the Macao Census and Statistics Department
today show that Macao had 414,000 permanent residents and 41,000
mobile residents on that day.
</P>
<P>
The department conducted the survey between August 30 and
September 8 this year.
</P>
<P>
Compared with the figures of the population census in 1991, the
number of permanent residents grew by an annual rate of 3.1
percent, while the number of mobile residents decreased by 7,000.
</P>
<P>
Geographically, 94.4 percent of residents live in the Macao
Peninsula, down two percent from that of 1991. But the population
in Macao's two islands rose by 10,000, up two percentage points.
</P>
<P>
The sex ratio remained the same as 1991 to be 48 percent and
52 percent for men and women.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the the statistics show that the family size of
Macao residents is becoming smaller, with the average population
of 3.45 per family in 1991 dropping to 3.31 per family now.
</P>
</TEXT>
