<HEADLINE> Chinese Brands Dominate Household Electrical Appliances Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 27 (Xinhua) -- Chinese-made household
electrical appliances have taken the lead in the domestic market,
a survey has revealed.
</P>
<P>
The survey, carried out in 100 department stores in 35 major
cities across China, has found that more Chinese brand household
electrical appliances were sold by the end of November this year,
compared with imported models.
</P>
<P>
The survey, carried out by China Economy Consultancy Company
under the State Statistics Bureau, found that Chinese-made air
conditioners, refrigerators and washing machines have taken a
market share of between 58 percent to 93 percent.
</P>
<P>
The ten most sought after refrigerators were all from China.
</P>
<P>
In the field of color TV sets, the survey found, Changhong,
Kongka, Beijing, Panda and other Chinese brands have jointly taken
65 percent of the market share.
</P>
<P>
The survey also noted that the monopoly of video players and
hi-fi systems marketed by overseas brands has been broken by
Chinese brands, and that Chinese companies control half of the
laser video CD players market.
</P>
<P>
However, experts warned Chinese companies of any premature
optimism, saying that big companies from abroad have switched
their ways of entering the Chinese market from selling their
products, technology and equipment, to selling their brands and
building factories in China, a more powerful way of enlarging
their market share.
</P>
<P>
They suggested that Chinese companies, in the course of
strengthening scientific research, readjust their assets and form
group companies in order to confront major foreign competitors.
</P>
</TEXT>
