<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Launches Large Garbage Processing Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 27 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka launched a major
garbage processing project estimated to cost 8.9 million US
dollars, according to Industrial Development Ministry sources
today.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that construction of the plant will soon
commence at Welisara in Colombo and is expected to be completed in
1998.
</P>
<P>
The sources noted that due to rapid urbanization in Sri Lanka,
garbage clearance has become a serious problem. There are no
suitable sites for garbage dumps available in Colombo city.
</P>
<P>
With the completion of the project, garbage of the entire city
could be treated in the plant, said the sources, adding that the
project is environmental friendly and all the garbage would be
converted into fertilizer.  
</P>
