<DATE_TIME> 1996-12-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Make Assets Administration Market-Oriented </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 27 (Xinhua) -- China should set up
state-owned holding companies to make its state assets
administration more market-oriented by the turn of the century, a
senior official has urged.
</P>
<P>
Reform of China's state assets administration system will
follow the direction of establishing a management, supervisory and
operational mechanism that well defines its rights and
responsibilities, vice minister of Finance Zhang Youcai said.
</P>
<P>
In management, the government's social and economic function
must be separated from that of the owner of state assets, said
Zhang, who is also director of the State Administration of State
Property, the industry watchdog.
</P>
<P>
Central and local governments should administer state assets at
different levels, he said, adding that specialized state assets
administration agencies must strictly perform their duties.
</P>
<P>
Zhang noted that supervision of state assets administration is
an all-round, multi-tier issue that should be tackled by
supervisory bodies at all levels.
</P>
<P>
The people's congress, China's legislative body, is mainly
responsible for supervision of the government's work in state
assets administration, while specialized assets administration
agencies should keep a watchful eye on investor subjects and the
operation of state assets.
</P>
<P>
The intermediary agencies should be responsible for supervision
of state assets operations and changes in property rights, and
enterprises should exercise self-restrain in state assets
management, he said.
</P>
<P>
Zhang warned that, except with some exceptions, government
departments must not operate state-owned assets directly.
</P>
<P>
He said that companies specializing in the operation of state
assets should be set up, adding that such firms should include
state-owned holding companies, state investment companies and
enterprise groups.
</P>
<P>
The companies, which are different from enterprises in the
ordinary sense, should be responsible for the safety and value
appreciation of state assets, Zhang noted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
