<HEADLINE> HK External Trade Continues To Grow in November </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 27 (Xinhua) -- The value of Hong Kong's
total exports in November this year increased by 5.1 percent over
the same month last year to 118.4 billion HK dollars (15.18
billion US dollars), while the value of imports rose by 4.9
percent to 131.1 billion HK dollars (16.8 billion US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Official statistics released today show that in November, a
visible trade deficit of 12.6 billion HK dollars (1.61 billion US
dollars) was recorded.
</P>
<P>
For the first eleven months as a whole, the value of total
exports rose by 4.3 percent over the same period last year, while
the value of imports showed an increase of three percent,
according to the statistics.
</P>
<P>
In the first eleven months, a visible trade deficit of 123
billion HK dollars (15.76 billion US dollars) was recorded, which
was smaller than the deficit of 134.7 billion HK dollars (17.27
billion US dollars) recorded in the same period last year. 
</P>
