<HEADLINE> East and South China Provinces Expand Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, December 27 (Xinhua) -- The regional cooperation
between east China's Fujian and Jiangxi provinces, and south
China's Guangd has made a substantial breakthrough, according to a
conference held here.
</P>
<P>
At the second joint conference of leaders from 13 cities and
prefectures of the provinces, officials have agreed to set up an
office in charge of the regional cooperation affairs, and elected
a permanent president and an executive president of the conference.
</P>
<P>
The specific moves signify that the provinces, which are an
important passage for goods from central and western China to
enter the world market, have upgraded the level of regional
operation,
</P>
<P>
At the conference, experts from the State Planning Commission
have divided the three provinces into four regional areas,
including special economic zones -- Xiamen and Shantou cities,
coastal areas -- Shanwei, Jieyang, Chaozhou, Zhangzhou and
Yingtan, central areas -- Meizhou, Longyan and Sanming, and
interior areas -- Ganzhou, Fuzhou and Yingtan.
</P>
<P>
The areas will join hands in infrastructure construction, and
setting up conglomerates of industrial enterprises, market
systems, and export-oriented economic system.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, since the first joint conference was held last year,
these provinces have made notable achievements in drafting joint
development plans, joint construction of traffic lines, and
transportation of goods between mountainous and coastal areas.
</P>
<P>
At present, Shantou, Shanwei, Chaozhou, Jieyang and Meizhou are
building highways together.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, construction of the Shantou-Jieyang-Meizhou
expressway will start in the coming five years.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the Zhangzhou-Chaoyang-Shantou Railway is being
prepared. Construction of the Xiamen-Quanzhou and Xiamen-Zhangzhou
expressways will be finished next year. And the the Guangdong and
Fujian sections of the 324 and 319 national highways have been
completed.  
</P>
</TEXT>
