<HEADLINE> Thai Auto Assembly Production Up Slightly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 27 (Xinhua) -- Automobiles assembled in
Thailand during January-November this year totaled 506,708 units,
up 4.96 percent compared with the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
According to the Automobile Industry Club of Thailand, among
these vehicles, assembled trucks numbered 375,222, up 3.37 percent
from the same period last year, while assembled cars posted
127,694 units, up 9.46 percent.
</P>
<P>
Factories around the country also assembled 2,280 station
wagons, 980 mini-buses and 529 10-ton coaches during the period.
</P>
<P>
However, motorcycles assembled in Thailand during the first 11
months this year totaled about 1.33 million units, down 19.76
percent from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
During the first 11 months this year, Thailand exported 10,684
assembled cars, up 60.1 percent from the same period last year,
earning 3.27 billion baht (129.1 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The country also exported 177,952 motorcycles worth 5.57
billion baht (222.7 million dollars) during the period.  
</P>
