<HEADLINE> HK Retail Sales on Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 27 (Xinhua) -- The value of Hong Kong's
total retail sales in October reached 19.1 billion HK dollars
(2.45 billion US dollars), an increase of seven percent over the
same month last year, according to official statistics released
today.
</P>
<P>
The statistics show that after discounting the effect of price
changes over the period, total retail sales rose two percent in
volume.
</P>
<P>
Compared with the same month last year, sales of motor vehicles
continued to record a significant increase, by 26 percent in value
and 25 percent in volume.
</P>
<P>
Sales of most other commodities also recorded increases of
various magnitudes in both value and volume terms, including
miscellaneous consumer goods, consumer durable goods, food,
alcoholic drinks and tobacco. Sales in supermarkets also went up
by 11 percent in value and four percent in volume.
</P>
<P>
Commodities which experienced decreases in sales include
jewelry, watches and clocks, fuels and valuable gifts.
</P>
<P>
Comparing the period from January to October with the same
period last year, total retail sales rose by six percent in value
and one percent in volume.  
</P>
</TEXT>
