<HEADLINE> Nigerian Currency May Appreciate Significantly in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, December 27 (Xinhua) -- The Nigerian currency,Naira may
appreciate significantly against U.S. dollar in the coming 1997, as
the government is planning a merger of the current dual exchange
rates.
</P>
<P>
The "Daily Times" reported today that the government has taken
major steps towards the alignment of the offcial and the Autonomous
Foreign Exchange Market rates at 56 Naira to one Dollar.
</P>
<P>
The currently official rate is 22 Naira to one Dollar, whereas the
rate at the Autonomous Foreign Exchange Market is 72 Naira to one
Follar.
</P>
<P>
The Naira has appreciated significantly in the last two weeks,
pushing the rate up from 80 Naira to one Dollar to 72 Naira to one
Dollar.
</P>
<P>
The report said this is due to the injection of dollars into the
market by the Nigerian authorities. But the official News Agency of
Nigeria said in an earlier report that the large number of Nigerians
returning from overseas with foreign currencies for Christmas has
forced the Dollar to Naira rate down.
</P>
<P>
Nigerian industry insiders have expressed the fear that the
proposed merger at lower rate is likely to attract criticism from the
World Bank, which has earlier proposed the merger rate of 95 Naira to
one Dollar to promote export of non-oil products.  
</P>
</TEXT>
