<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 27 (Xinhua) -- British Queen Elizabeth II has
lost more than half of her Christmas Day viewers over the past six
years.
</P>
<P>
This year's message was watched by a total of ll million TV
viewers, a drop of nearly three million in just l2 months,
according to unofficial estimates.
</P>
<P>
The decline in interest in the message will dismay the Queen
who has regarded the broadcast as one of her most significant
duties of the year, said the British newspaper, the Guardian.
</P>
<P>
This year's message, which urged victims of tragedy to look
forward with hope, was the last for two years to be produced by
the BBC. 
