<HEADLINE> Philippines' Exports From Industrial Manufactures Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 27 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines' export
earnings from industrial manufactures rose 32.72 percent during
the first 10 months of this year, the Bureau of Export Trade
Promotion (BETP) said today.
</P>
<P>
Data from the BETP show that for the first 10 months, sales
overseas from this commodity group jumped to 10.688 billion US
dollars from 8.053 billion dollars recorded in the same period
last year.
</P>
<P>
Industrial manufactures accounted for 83.59 percent of the
total export earnings for the period which stood at 16.809 billion
US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Strong demand for electronics boosted the sales of industrial
manufactures, the BETP said. The electronics sector continued to
exhibit impressive sales performance in the 10-month period, as it
toppled all other groups under industrial manufactures.
</P>
<P>
For the past months, exports revenue from electronics continued
to swell by 41.06 percent. Exports of semiconductor devices
dominated the bulk by raking in 6.953 billion US dollars during
the period.
</P>
<P>
Machinery and transport equipment garnered the second highest
earnings which amounted to 617.311 million US dollars, up 8.4
percent from a year ago's level of 569.500 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Despite the 10.17 percent drop in export revenues during the
period, metal manufactures made the third largest earnings valued
at 438.482 million US dollars, dipping from last year's 488.116
million.
</P>
<P>
Other groups which contributed considerable dollar receipts
were petroleum products, chemicals, construction materials,
textile yarns and fabrics. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
