<HEADLINE> Maputo Urged To Offer More Investment Facilities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO,December 27 (Xinhua) --Mozambicans living in some
southern African countries have called uopn the Mozambican
government to provide more facilities for their investment in the
country.
</P>
<P>
Mozambican immigrants in South Africa, Swaziland and Zimbabwe
made the call in a letter which was delivered to Mozambican
President Joaquim Chissano yesterday, the local newspaper " Noticias"
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The overseas Mozambicans have asked, among others, for more
simple procedures for investment, exemption of visas when they return
to Mozambique and higher interest rate for their deposit in
Mozambican banks.
</P>
<P>
Chissano will meet the Mozambican cabinet members to discuss
with them what answers should be made to the letter from the
overseas Mozambicans, said the report. 
</P>
