<HEADLINE> ICBC Offers 500 Million Yuan Loans for Airport Road Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 27 (Xinhua) -- Industrial and Commercial
Bank of China (ICBC) Shanghai Pudong Branch today provided 500
million yuan in loans for the construction of Far East Avenue, a
thoroughfare leading to Shanghai Pudong International Airport.
</P>
<P>
The loans are the largest single lending by local banks for the
development of Pudong New Area in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The Far East Avenue will be 14 km long and 100 meters wide,
with six speedy lanes and two slow tracks.
</P>
<P>
The expressway project, scheduled to be completed by the end of
next year, will link up the new international airport with the
city's inner circle road and No.2 Subway.
</P>
<P>
Once the road project is finished, Shanghai's two international
airports -- the existing Hongqiao and the new one in Pudong now
under construction -- will be connected.
</P>
<P>
The bank branch, the largest banking institution in Pudong, has
granted some three billion yuan in the development area, and now
it plans to open a sub-branch in the area of the new international
airport in Pudong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
