<HEADLINE> Commercial Bank Taking Shape In Pudong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 27 (Xinhua) -- The Pudong Development Bank in
Shanghai, which was founded four years ago, has developed into a
share-holding commercial bank.
</P>
<P>
By the end of November, it had taken savings deposits totalling
37 billion yuan, and its assets amounted to 70 billion yuan in
value.
</P>
<P>
The bank has opened 28 branches in Beijing, Shanghai, Hangzhou,
capital of Zhejiang Province, and other places.
</P>
<P>
Ever since its establishment, the bank has supported the
construction of the urban infrastructural facilities such as the
Pudong International Airport, the No. 2 Subway and a tunnel
beneath the Huangpu River that flows through Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The bank is helping increase the value of the insurance fund
for pensioners and has issued China's first computerized banking
card called "Oriental Card".
</P>
<P>
A bank official said that his bank will try to promote the
development of the Pudong Development Zone and the regional
economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
