<HEADLINE> 14 Local Telephone Networks Operational in Hubei </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, December 27 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Hubei Province
has expanded 14 local telephone networks, and put them into formal
operation, according to the province's posts and telecommunications
administration.
</P>
<P>
Along with the launching of 14 local webs, the province's last
batch of six-digit telephone numbers, which are used in the
prefectures of Jingsha, Shiyan and Jingmen, was upgraded to seven
digits on the mid-night of December 15.
</P>
<P>
Liang Qingzhang, director of the administration, said that the
telephone number upgrading will greatly improve the operation of
local telecom networks, and provide more "phone number resource"
to the province's growing telephone market.
</P>
<P>
He said that these local networks will be accessible to such
new telecom functions as the intelligent, broadband and personal
communications services, and, most importantly, will largely cut
people's phone bill by calculating the long-distance calls on
the basis of local call charges.
</P>
<P>
So far, Hubei has more than 2.8 million phone subscribers, and
the telephone density rate increased from 0.68 per cent in
1990 to 5.5 per cent in 1996.  
</P>
</TEXT>
