<HEADLINE> Philippine President Grants Aid to Disaster Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 27 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel
Ramos today approved the release of 20 million pesos (7.6 million
US dollars) for the rehabilitation of damaged infrastructure
projects in the central province of Catanduanes.
</P>
<P>
Ramos said the money was in addition to the 30 million pesos
(11.4 million US dollars) earlier released to Catanduanes from the
reserves of the Department of the Budget and Management Office of
the President.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching the Presidential Palace said five days of
torrential rains had triggered massive landslides and flooding in
the province in late November, resulting in heavy damage to public
works projects.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine National Disaster Coordinating Council (NDCC)
reported that 13 persons died, seven were injured, and one was
reported missing when the landslides hit. The total damage to
government infrastructure was estimated at 135 million pesos.
</P>
