<HEADLINE> China's Phone Switching Capacity Exceeds 100 Million Lines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 27 (Xinhua) -- China added 15 million lines
to its telephone switching capacity this year, bringing the total
to 100 million lines, according to today's overseas edition of
People's Daily.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the telephone density rate was improved to 6.2 per
cent, compared with the 4.66 per cent of 1995.
</P>
<P>
The business volume of post and telecommunications is expected
to hit 133 billion yuan, up 34.5 per cent over that of last year.
</P>
<P>
So far, China has its data telecom network extend to all the
cities and counties, and established a uniform walkie-talkie
network countrywide.
</P>
<P>
In the urban areas, about 22 per cent of households have been
equipped with telephones, the paper said.  
</P>
