<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Rice Production Predicted to Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, December 27 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia will produce 51
million tons of unhusked rice this year, up from 49.74 million
tons last year, local press today quoted a senior official as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Agriculture Sjarifudin Baharsjah said Thursday that
this figure was still lower than the initial target of 51.6
million tons.
</P>
<P>
He said 50.03 million tons of unhusked rice was equivalent to
32 million tons of rice.
</P>
<P>
With an annual consumption rate of 130 kilograms of rice per
capita, the country's 195 million people were estimated to eat
25.9 million tons of rice this year, the minister said.  
</P>
