<HEADLINE> Hunan Province Meets Grain-Purchasing Target </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, December 27 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Hunan
Province has hit a target by purchasing nearly 3.2 billion
kilograms of grain from farmers this year, up 270 million kg over
1995.
</P>
<P>
The province, a major rice production center in China, has met
its grain purchasing quota despite great losses in grain
production caused by flooding and water-logging disasters.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to greater efforts exerted to fight against the
disasters, the province has achieved a good grain harvest this
year, with grain output expected to total 26.5 billion kg, only
one billion kg less than the local record-year volume.
</P>
<P>
Farmers in areas unaffected, or only slightly hit by the
disasters, have delivered nearly 73 million kg of grain to aid the
disaster-stricken regions, helping people overcome difficulties.
</P>
</TEXT>
