<HEADLINE> Shijiazhuang Airport Opens to Foreign Airplanes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, December 27 (Xinhua) -- Shijiazhuang Airport, in
the capital of north China's Hebei Province, has just opened to
foreign airplanes. The first chartered airplane, which belongs to
a Russian airline, landed on the airport Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Two international air routes from Shijiazhuang to Russia and
Ukraine have been in service. The provincial civil aviation
administration says that air routes from the Chinese city to other
members of the Commonwealth of Independent States will also open
in the near future.
</P>
<P>
Shijiazhuang boasts two of China's top ten trade markets. The
city is speeding up construction and expansion of markets and
production bases, to ensure trade exchanges with eastern European
countries, especially when air links have been set up.
</P>
