<HEADLINE> Yunnan's First Thermal Power Project Goes on Line </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, December 27 (Xinhua) -- A thermal power generating unit
with a capacity of 200,000 KW, the first of its kind in southwest
China's Yunnan Province, has gone into operation.
</P>
<P>
The unit was installed by the Yangzonghai Generating
Co. Ltd. in its first phase of construction.
</P>
<P>
In its second phase, 200,000-kw generating unit will be
installed in 1998.
</P>
<P>
A local official said that construction of the thermal power
project is designed to ease the province's power shortage during
the dry season.
</P>
<P>
Crisscrossed by rivers, Yunnan abounds in hydroelectric
resources and is encouraging all sectors to invest in its power
industry.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of the Yangzonghai Generating Co. Ltd. is a
result of that kind of cooperation. 
</P>
