<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Largest Exhibition of Bird Fossils to Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 27 (Xinhua) -- China's largest exhibition of
bird fossils will open in Beijing on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition, the largest of kind in China and even in the
world, will display 300 specimen of 200 kinds of bird fossils,
according to noted ornithologist Hou Lianhai.
</P>
<P>
On display will be precious fossils of ancient birds, such as
Confuciusornis, Liaoningornis, Cachayornis, Chaoyangra, Wanshuina,
Songzia and Diatrymiformes, Hou said.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition will mainly display the fossils of birds which
lived in the Mesozoic Era 65 to 225 million years ago, said Hou, a
research fellow with the Institute of Vertebrate Paleontology and
Paleoanthropology, the Chinese Academy of Sciences.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition aims to display Chinese scientists' research
findings in ornithology, and spread the knowledge of the evolution
of the bird, he said.
</P>
<P>
The two-month exhibition will be held in a 100 sq-m hall in the
China Ancient Creatures Museum. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
