<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, December 27 (Xinhua) -- The medical authorities in
Livingstone in southern Zambia, have declared the tourist capital
as rabies infected area and an extensive rabies awareness
campaign will be launched there soon.
</P>
<P>
The declaration followed the outbreak of the disease which has
killed four people so far, the local newspaper ''Daily Mail''
reported today.
</P>
<P>
District Health Officer Jelita Chinyonga has advised residents
to be wary of stray dogs in the townships and suburbs.
</P>
<P>
She said, ''There has been a typical outbreak of rabies which
has killed about four people but the number could be more because
of some cases which have not been reported to our department.''
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the district veterinary department has embarked on
a massive vaccination program in a bit to prevent the spread of
the disease in the district.
</P>
<P>
Livingstone is by the world-known Victoria Falls attracting
large numbers of tourists to come. 
