<HEADLINE> Foreign Funds Boost Anhui's Machinery Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 27 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province
has introduced foreign investment to its machinery sector in a
move to improve technology and increase exports.
</P>
<P>
So far this year, the province has approved eight
foreign-funded machinery enterprises involving 200 million US
dollars in total investment and with a combined registered capital
of 189 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Over the past five years, Anhui's machinery sector has brought
in a combined investment of 388 million US dollars from overseas
companies, and launched 69 enterprises altogether.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the foreign-funded enterprises scored a total
turnover of more than one billion yuan, and made 57.55
million yuan in profits.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics show that these enterprises exported 14
million dollars worth of products in 1995, 13.55 percent of the
total of the machinery industry.
</P>
<P>
Along with the foreign capital, advanced technologies and
managerial expertise were also introduced to the inland province.
In the last five years, such hi-tech machinery equipment as
digital-controlled machine tools and fork trucks were put into
extensive use there.  
</P>
