<HEADLINE> Ukraine's Nuclear Plants Exceed Annual Estimates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, December 26 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine's nuclear power plants
generated 2.4 percent more electricity than planned in 1996, the
country's National Committee of Nuclear Energy said today.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine's five nuclear plants produced 79 billion kilowatt
hours (kwh) this year, an increase of 12.7 percent over 1995, the
committee said.
</P>
<P>
Although Chernobyl's No. 1 reactor was shut down at the end of
November, the five plants generated 43.8 percent of the country's
total electricity.
</P>
<P>
However, the installed capacity of the five nuclear plants as a
proportion within the national total is considerably less than
indicated by the electricity they generated.
</P>
<P>
There are altogether 14 reactors running in these nuclear
plants, which include Chernobyl. 
