<HEADLINE> Dabie Mountains Rich in Mineral Resources </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, December 27 (Xinhua) -- Geologists have discovered
large deposits of non-ferrous metals, precious metals and other
minerals in the Dabie Mountains in central China.
</P>
<P>
The mountains have a complex geological structure, with good
conditions for the formation of minerals, geologists said.
</P>
<P>
A contingent of 700 geological workers in central China's Henan
Province have worked all round year to prospect and look for
mineral resources since 1950s, and conducted surveys in the
mountains, which have drawn the attention of geologists worldwide.
</P>
<P>
In late 1960s, geologists discovered an unusually large
non-ferrous ore in the Xinyang County.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, they discovered successively two high-grade silver
ore in Luoshan County, a number of small gold mines in Guangshan
County, and mines containing both gold and silver resources in
Shangcheng County over recent years.
</P>
<P>
This year, a copper mine with a three-km formation structure
and great potential for development, was found in Xinxian County.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
