<HEADLINE> Sino-Canadian Timber Market to Be Built in Fujian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, December 27 (Xinhua) -- A contract on building the
largest timber market in Fujian was signed in this provincial
capital city recently.
</P>
<P>
The timber market, a Sino-Canadian joint venture, will be the
fourth regional trading center for forest products in China. The
other three locate in northeast China's Jilin Province, Luoyang
City in central China's Henan Province and Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The venture will cover 11.5 ha of land in Zhangzhou, where
there are 610,000 ha of forests with a timber reserve of 15
million cubic meters. The city turns out 200,000 cubic meters of
marketable timber annually.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the market will cost an investment of 88
million yuan, the major part of which will be provided by the D
and E International Company Ltd. of Canada.
</P>
<P>
The first phase of the project includes construction of three
commercial-residential buildings and 309 vendor's stands with a
total floor space of 98,000 sq.m. It will be completed in two
years. 
</P>
