<HEADLINE> Shanghai's Urban Families' Income Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 27 (Xinhua) -- A sample survey shows that
the real income of urban families in Shanghai, the largest
manufacturing center in China, will average 25,000 yuan (3,015
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
According to the survey, conducted among 500 families, the real
average income of urban families reached 21,000 yuan in the
first ten months of this year.
</P>
<P>
Total earnings of urban families consist of wages and the
non-wage income.
</P>
<P>
In the first ten months of 1996, wages accounted for 59 percent
of total earnings of Shanghai families, a rise of three percentage
points from the same period in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, earnings from non-wage sources contributed 40.6
percent to total earnings, a drop of 3.1 percentage point.
</P>
<P>
The wage-oriented income of Shanghai's urban residents shot up
by 20.5 percent and the non-wage income rose by 5.9 percent only
in the first ten months of this year.
</P>
<P>
Experts agreed that with the success in the price reform, the
price increase range has decreased substantially, with the result
that local residents' incomes have been increasing steadily. 
</P>
</TEXT>
