<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, December 27 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese University of
Science and Technology held a two-day job fair recently, inviting
hundreds of research institutes and enterprises to send people to
talk face-to-face with its graduating students on the campus.
</P>
<P>
Over 400 graduates signed contracts with their employers at the
fair, according to the school in east China's Anhui province.
</P>
<P>
"We hope graduating students will find jobs according to their
wish. That's the purpose of our fair," said Xu Ping, organizer of
the fair.
</P>
