<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 27 (Xinhua) -- A sophisticated digital
telecommunications network will link all the cities and counties
of east China's land-locked Jiangxi Province next summer.
</P>
<P>
According the Beijing-based People's Posts and
Telecommunications News, the province's DDN (digital data network)
has been expanded twice this year.
</P>
<P>
The third expansion project which is scheduled for completion
in mid-1997 will extend the web to every corner of the
province.
</P>
<P>
The number of the network's subscribers will increase by 1,000
this year, with the total reaching 2,000. The increase margin
will be 1,000 users next year, said a local telecommunications
official.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, a Internet branch will be launched in Jiangxi next
year. Through a local node, the branch will connect the province
with the global computer web, via Chinanet, an affiliate Chinese
network.
</P>
<P>
The number of Internet subscribers will reach 250 in the
province next year, the paper said. 
</P>
