making greater contributions to local economic development in east
China's Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
The province has approved 2,500 Taiwan-funded businesses, with
a total investment worth more than five billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
While raising funds to support the development of Taiwan firms,
local governments have promulgated special regulations in favor of
these enterprises. Provincial leaders have also maintained direct
contacts with 20 selected Taiwan businesses to help them solve
difficulties.
</P>
