<HEADLINE> New Replacement For Trachea Is Used </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SICHUAN, December 26 (Xinhua) -- A hospital in Chongqing in
southwest China's Sichuan Province successfully used the flap of
pectoralis major to replace the trachea in a patient on November
27.
</P>
<P>
Daping Hospital is the first to perform such an operation in
China. The patient, 51, is quite well after operation.
</P>
<P>
At the end of the 1980s, the flap of pectoralis major was used
to replace esophagus in the neck in some cases abroad. However,
the replacement of trachea with the flap has never been reported,
said Jiang Yaoguang, the leading operator of the case.
</P>
<P>
"The pectoralis major is near the trachea, and its blood
circulation is good. Therefore, it is a good replacement for the
trachea," he explained.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
