<HEADLINE> Paper Packaging Industry Bridges Gap Between Shenzhen, HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, December 27 (Xinhua) -- The paper packaging industry
in China's first special economic zone of Shenzhen plays a vital
role in promoting the city's economic links with Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Shenzhen has 700 packaging firms, accounting for half of the
total of Guangdong Province, where the city is located.
</P>
<P>
The annual output value of the industry in the city tops five
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
About ten percent of the city's paper packaging products are
exported to Europe, America, Japan and southeast Asia, while the
rest are packaging materials for export goods manufactured in
Shenzhen and other parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
The Packaging industry started in Shenzhen in the 1980s, when
95 percent of Hong Kong's packaging manufacturers had to move to
Shenzhen, as a result of skyrocketing land prices and expensive
labor services in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong has made enormous investment in Shenzhen's packaging
industry and most of the city's goods orders are from Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
More than 60 percent of the packaging materials for the two
places are made in Shenzhen. And the ratio will shoot up sharply
after Hong Kong returns to the embrace of the motherland in July
next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
