<HEADLINE> Scientific Stamps A Hit in Auction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, December 27 (Xinhua) -- A box of some 100 mini-sheet
stamps featuring a girl and her imagined scientific world has been
sold at 550,000 yuan at an auction held in this capital of
northwest China's Shaanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
The stamp, "Loving Science from Childhood", was published in
the late 1970s, at a face value of five yuan.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that it appreciated most sharply among Chinese
stamps issued in the past four decades.
</P>
<P>
The most appreciated single stamp at the auction, however, is a
yellow stamp issued exclusively for servicemen over 40 years
ago. It was sold at 70,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
A total of 120 stamps and 81 pieces of Chinese paintings and
calligraph were sold at the auction. 
</P>
</TEXT>
