<HEADLINE> Northwest China Building Largest Coal Mining Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, December 27 (Xinhua) -- Gansu Province, northwest
China, is accelerating construction of northwest China's largest
coal mining area.
</P>
<P>
Upon completion within 10 years, the Huating mining area will
have five key collieries forming an annual production capacity of
10.15 million tons.
</P>
<P>
With verified reserves of 3.26 billion tons of quality coal,
the mining area will require an investment of more than 2.6
billion yuan in construction.
</P>
<P>
With its construction work started in December 1991, the
Chenjiagou mine, the first one with an annual designed capacity of
450,000 tons, has gone into production.
</P>
<P>
The Yanbei Coal Mine, which has been listed as a major project
during the Eighth Five-Year Plan (1996-2000) and is the second one
with an annual designed capacity of three million tons, is now
well under construction.
</P>
<P>
A local official said that construction of the remaining three
mines will begin soon, and, upon their completion, they will make
Gansu one of the leading coal producers in the country.  
</P>
