<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Early Development of "Death Canyons" in Mt. Changbai Urged (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, December 27 (Xinhua) -- Mention Ganfanpen to people
in northeast China and they quiver. It's a place where few humans
have dared to tread and lived to tell the tale.
</P>
<P>
Ganfanpen in Jilin Province, is known as China's 'death
canyon', an inland Bermuda Triangle where mysterious happenings
defy the laws of science.
</P>
<P>
Experienced hunters and collectors of precious ginseng have
headed into the arms of Ganfanpen, and never been seen again.
</P>
<P>
Compasses, a vital lifesaver for explorers, are useless in
death canyon - the needle will go haywire. And a bizarre
phenomenon disorientates people and affects their memories. They end
up going round in circles, unable to escape again to the outside
world.
</P>
<P>
Yet despite the dangers, tourism experts believe that the
canyons could become a money spinning tourism attraction for China.
</P>
<P>
They believe that the mystery and the magic of Ganfanpen,
situated in the Changbai Mountains, could lure visitors to
experience one of the world's most unique attractions.
</P>
<P>
Ganfanpen, which was named by local residents, is a series of
special canyons consisting of similar mountains and gullies in
deep primeval forests in Changbai Mountains.
</P>
<P>
Even experienced local people often lose their way. People in
the canyons often head in the opposite direction to the correct
way, and no matter how far they go, they inevitably return to the
original place, unable to find a way out of a cruel maze.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19961227.0205 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-12-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Early Development of "Death Canyons" in Mt. Changbai Urged (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Compasses also indicate wrong directions in the canyons.
</P>
<P>
Some experts believe that Ganfanpen, with its rarely seen
circular canyons without cliffs, are mysterious prehistoric canyon
relics.
</P>
<P>
Other experts claim that the canyons were shaped by falling
ancient meteorites. As the space-invading rocks formed strong
magnetic fields, the human biological clock becomes imbalanced,
and people's memories are disordered, causing visitors to lose
their way.
</P>
<P>
Several death canyons have been discovered in Changbai
Mountains, with the most famous located in Jiangyuan County,
126.50 degrees east longitude and 42 degrees north latitude.
</P>
<P>
The grand canyon, 20 kilometers long and 15 kilometers in
width, occupies a space of 300 square kilometers. The basin-shaped
canyon groups together 81 small basins.
</P>
<P>
The canyon is surrounded by many forest-covered mountains,
without a main peak.
</P>
<P>
As very few people have ventured into the canyon in thousands
of years, primeval forests are still well preserved, with many
wild beasts living there.
</P>
<P>
According to an old man living near the canyon, during the
eight-year Anti-Japanese War (1937 to 1945), an Anti-Japanese
troop stored their weapons and food in one canyon, and over 100
Japanese soldiers and their puppet army pursued them.
</P>
<P>
In the end, the old man said, all of the enemy troops died in
the canyon after losing their way, and two planes, sent by the
Japanese to rescue them also crashed to the ground when they flew
over the canyon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19961227.0206 </DOCNO>
