advice.
</P>
<P>
The local health bureau hopes to reform residents' unhealthy
living habits through various activities and to cut down the
incidence of chronic diseases in the city.
</P>
<P>
As in other Chinese cities, chronic illnesses, including
vascular diseases of the heart or brain and malignant tumors,
have become the major health threats in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that deaths from such chronic ailments
accounted for more than 64 percent of deaths from illness in 1994.
</P>
<P>
Some 30,000 people die from vascular diseases of the heart or
brain in Beijing each year.  
