<HEADLINE> Hebei's Industry Moves in High Gear </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, December 27 (Xinhua) -- The past decade has
witnessed the fastest industrial growth in north China's Hebei
Province, according to a survey conducted by the provincial
statistics bureau.
</P>
<P>
The survey shows that the value of Hebei's total industrial
assets soared to 381.33 billion yuan at the end of 1995, about
eight times that in 1985.
</P>
<P>
The sales of industrial products stood at 347.73 billion yuan
last year, 8.7 times that of 1985.
</P>
<P>
Production of coal, electricity, timber, fabrics, chemical
fertilizers, cement and plate glass, has at least doubled since
1985.
</P>
<P>
Hebei now contributes 16.38 percent to the country's annual
plate glass production.
</P>
<P>
Over the past ten years, such basic industries as energy and
raw materials have been going full steam ahead as well.
</P>
<P>
The province's backbone industries, including foodstuffs,
beverages, tobacco, building materials and electric equipment,
have also shown strong momentum.
</P>
<P>
Ten percent of Hebei residents are employed in 229,715
enterprises, according to the results of the survey. 
</P>
