<HEADLINE> Lone Sailor in Trouble Boards Life Raft </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 26 (Xinhua) -- A French sailor in high freak
seas in a solo round-the-world race has boarded a life raft
dropped by an Australian rescue plane on Thursday, according to
reports here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Australian plane began a search for Raphael Dinelli after
he set off distress signals from his yacht Algimouss, some 1,200
nautical miles southwest of Western Australia, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the Vendee Globe race said Dinelli, 28, boarded
the raft and he appeared to be safe.
</P>
<P>
Australian Maritime Safety Authority (AMSA) spokesman David
Gray earlier told reporters that Dinelli had set off distress
signals early on Thursday morning as the yacht met heavy seas and
winds.  
</P>
</TEXT>
