<HEADLINE> World Bank Finances Rural Infrastructure in Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 26 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today
announced the approval of a credit equivalent to some 55 million
U.S. dollars for the rural transport project in Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
The credit will be channeled through the International
Development Association (IDA), the concessionary lending wing of
the World Bank for the project.
</P>
<P>
The rural transport project is the first IDA operation
supporting rural infrastructure in the country. It is designed to
boost poverty alleviation and rural development efforts by
upgrading the network of rural access roads in 15 of the country's
poorest provinces. Community participation and use of local
contractors will be an important component of the project, and a
rural transport study will be undertaken to establish guidelines
for future rural infrastructure investment.
</P>
<P>
The estimated total project cost is 60.89 million dollars. In
addition to the IDA credit, the Vietnamese government will
contribute some 5.89 million dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
